I love this granola and make it several times a week! After making it so frequently, thought I'd pass on a few tips for folks if they're interested. I cut down on the amount of oil and it doesn't seem to matter. I've also used all honey and brown sugar with good effect. Finally, for those who have trouble getting the granola to clump: as soon as the granola is finished baking (still warm and slightly moist, pack it up into a tight bar by wrapping it in foil and throw it in the freezer. By pushing the granola into itself, it will solidify as a bar that can then be broken apart when cool. Works wonderfully! Enjoy.

