To the cook from Boston who wondered about clumps. I haven't made this recipe, but I followed Cook's Illustrated recipe that gave the following instructions for clumpy granola: For clumpy granola, right after you remove the mixture from the oven, press it into a three-quarter-inch layer with even edges, then press a single layer of paper towels onto the granola. When the granola is cool, remove the towels. Remove the cereal in sections and place in an airtight container. When ready to use, crumble granola to desired chunkiness.

